  title: Paintings
  description: 'Portraits displayed in dining rooms often represented members of
    the family, important relatives, or distinguished guests. These paintings were
    not only decorative but also served to communicate wealth, lineage, and social
    connections. In many cases, they reinforced the status of the household within
    local society. '
